guduz :  Yet another RED simulator (YaREDs)

Mehmet Suzen  <mehmet.suzen@physics.org>
Ziya Suzen  <zsuzen@acm.org>

October 2006


The Internet Traffic  congestion avoidance algorithms are becoming curicial
for the traffic optimization, fair use of resources and quality of service. 
guduz or YaREDs is a simple and flexiable implementation of Random Early Detection 
algorithm of Sally Floyd, Van Jacobson. It can be used as an educational tool or
to understand the basics of the RED algorithm.

Please look at the docs directory for example results and how to use 
the code. Further comments and suggestions you can drop us an email



[1] Sally Floyd, Van Jacobson August 1993 IEEE/ACM Transactions in Networking

